re. This work seems to have functioned as a source of feed for any interested orator. In the Introduction and the footnotes, in addition to the Nikolaos Kataphloron biography, the questions about the recipient’s prosopography, the historical context in which the text was composed and its date, they are discussed issues related to the education, the rhetoric and more generally the literature of Comnenian era.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aByzanz /Kultur. 4aByzanz /Literatur. 4aKonstantinopel. 4aNikolaos Kataphlôron.  aByzantine Aristocracy.  aByzantine Language and Culture.  aMedieval Athens.  aRhetoric.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019z9783110605945oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311063386340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311063471640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110634716423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110634716/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019